Ok we have a lot of sorcerers (and sorceresses) down in the dumps...<P>I saw the post where Merwyn posted His "RVR Success stories" and thought mabey we could all use a break for a second from negativity. How about everyone share the funnest moment (rvr OR pve) that you remember in your carreer.<P>Mine has to be when I was on the Goblin Hunter Bow quest in Camp forest. I finished off the quest and noticed a Goblin Magician. He conned yellow to me, and I thought "hmm what the heck". Released the Goblin Hunter I currently had and Charmed the magician... <BR>Watching your pet use Nukes has to be one of the funnest things I've ever seen. I took him up the trail with me, and the two of us hunted Oak men. It was real blast selecting the Oak man, hitting "attack" and watching my Goblin get into postion and start nuking away. (plus those fire casting animations are darn nice).<P>Anyhow thought we could all use a little break and mabey share stories (mabey even Bullseye would share a story here?)<P>--------------------<P>It's not a dress damnit! It's a Fine Manly Robe!!
