<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
One day just to test a theory i started charming bandits near the entrance to Salisbury plains. many people come here to hunt the bandits and the filidhs slightly up the hill from here, especially since you can bind at the bridge. As i did i started charming a target, sending it to attack another, and then releasing it. I would then charm another and sent it after the last oen i had just charmed.<P>All in all i had about 16 bandits and filidhs in a grand melee with noone controlling them. Once they start fighting, they continue after you release.<P>Pointless, but funny to watch everyone try to figure out what the hell i was doing.<P>I even used this constructively once to split the slaver spawn. then after the ende i kept one pet and started pulling sinlges as they popped.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
