<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well this isn't so much a success story as a funny learning experience story, but here goes =)<P> The first time I went to Lyonesse I was by myself and thought I would have fun with the peallaidhs. Most were orange and red, but there was a lone yellow, so i moved around biding my time waiting for him to be in range. Noticed he was a scout when I targeted, but i had not encountered scout monsters before so I didn't think it was anything to be concerned with. Finally he gets close enough, and i cast my charm, and it tells me he's in combat. Normally quick on the uptake but a little baffled by this, I stood around for about 10 seconds thinking, since nothing else was nearby, when all of a sudden I see what looks like an army of peallaidhs rushing from the waters edge at me. Being that far from a bind point I didn't take the time to count, but there had to have been at least 5 of the buggers rushing after me. Unfortunately, since my speed was negated, i didn't make it away, but it was the most fun i've probably ever had dying.<P>Lesson to be learned: Scout monsters are bad, very bad, unless you have a good group and use them to pull for you. If they spot you, you'll know by your speed dropping and getting the in combat recently message, and if you hang around long enough you'll see an army of critters running after you. <P><BR>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Enigmatic of 40 seasons on Percival<BR>Proud member of The Dawn's Chosen
