Scouts are ALWAYS the first choice to charm, because they cause so much trouble if left to their own devices. they run FAST, but unfortunately this run speed does not carry over once they are enslaved, and i have no idea why. I know when a hunter charms a cat it still moves at the high rate a speed a cat always does.<P>Hmmm.....<P>Gonna ask about this one. We really should have our pets maintain their original movement rates as an advantage or disadvantage of picking that particular slave.<P>BTW- casting confusion on a MOB a group is fighting wihtout them knowing it can be HELL. It is borderline griefing, and can seriously ruin a groups day. Also, if they have a healer, you can break soemone elses Mez with the confusion. Now guess who is on the list of whom to kill for that MOB? thats right, just you and the healer.<P>Once we have a full amnesia I am wondering if it will break Mez or not. If it does this also becomes a rather nasty tactic. All this can be used for griefing, but can be AMAZING if you catch an enemy group unaware in the frontier.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
