Allright, I do have my favorite RvR experience.  It wasn't a victory; it was a defeat.  But it was a grand defeat.<P>Me and a friend were at the Albion side wall in the Hibernian frontier.  There's was a battle going on...of course, they lined up at their side, we at our wall.  My friend and I decided to take a long route around the hill, and then come up behind the army.  To be killed, of course, but all in the name of enjoyment and adventure.<P>We go for awhile, get lost a little, but eventually end up behind the wall.  We see some bodies of our dead colleagues, and not far off, a young Elf lass attending to a cat pet of hers.  We go up, glad to see some adventure, and engage the poor girl.  Alas, she doesn't run, and knows she is going to die.  Sensible of her, which she recieved a salute after her demise.<P>At this point, a few scattered reinforcements arrive.  My friend, an Armsmen, runs off to deal with his counterpart, while I set my eyes on my own, an Elf caster waving his hands at me.<P>At first, the spell hits me, and takes quite a bit of damage.  I know the next will kill me, so what do I do?  I run, but not away....no, I run straight at the guy!<P>In fact, before he finishes the spell, I run right through him, and behind him.  The spell fails, as he lost sight of me and didn't think to keep his hands on the flippin' keyboard to turn around and follow me.  So he spins around, and starts waving his arms again, the deathspell on his lips.<P>So what I do is get up real close to him, and hit him square on the forehead with my staff.  Again, this cancels the poor Elf's spell.  And unfortunately, I even damaged my staff a little with that one hit<P>At last, he wises up, and quickcast the dang thing on me, while keeping me in sight.  <P>At least I cancelled two of his spells, which may have gained valuable moments for my friend to also die with me.<P>~Sigma<BR>26 Sorcerer<BR>Percival
</FONT>
